            True since LHS = EL n [] = RHS       by MAP3_DEF
         Otherwise, lz = h''::t'.
            to show: EL n (MAP3 f (h::lx) (h'::t) (h''::t')) <= EL n (MAP3 g (h::lx) (h'::t) (h''::t'))
            If n = 0,
                EL 0 (MAP3 f (h::lx) (h'::t) (h''::t'))
